session_history.content: educate yourself on the table dds of fitness_db

The fitness_db database contains the following tables: Products, SaleDetails, ServiceTickets, Sales, and Customers, each with its own defined structure and constraints as described in their respective DDL statements.

Key Observations

  • The Products table stores information about the products, including ProductID, ProductName, ProductType, Brand, Price, and StockQuantity.
  • The SaleDetails table records details of each sale, referencing Sales and Products tables using foreign keys (SaleID, ProductID).
  • The ServiceTickets table tracks customer service requests, linking to Customers and Products tables via foreign keys (CustomerID, ProductID).
  • The Sales table stores sales transactions, linking to the Customers table via a foreign key (CustomerID).
  • The Customers table contains customer information, including contact details, address, and registration date.

CREATE MULTISET TABLE fitness_db.Products ,FALLBACK ,
     NO BEFORE JOURNAL,
     NO AFTER JOURNAL,
     CHECKSUM = DEFAULT,
     DEFAULT MERGEBLOCKRATIO,
     MAP = TD_MAP1
     (
      ProductID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      ProductName VARCHAR(100) CHARACTER SET LATIN NOT CASESPECIFIC NOT NULL,
      ProductType VARCHAR(50) CHARACTER SET LATIN NOT CASESPECIFIC,
      Brand VARCHAR(50) CHARACTER SET LATIN NOT CASESPECIFIC,
      Price DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
      StockQuantity INTEGER)
UNIQUE PRIMARY INDEX ( ProductID );
SQL DDL: fitness_db.SaleDetails 
CREATE MULTISET TABLE fitness_db.SaleDetails ,FALLBACK ,
     NO BEFORE JOURNAL,
     NO AFTER JOURNAL,
     CHECKSUM = DEFAULT,
     DEFAULT MERGEBLOCKRATIO,
     MAP = TD_MAP1
     (
      SaleDetailID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      SaleID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      ProductID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      Quantity INTEGER NOT NULL,
      UnitPrice DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL, 
FOREIGN KEY ( SaleID ) REFERENCES fitness_db.Sales ( SaleID ),
FOREIGN KEY ( ProductID ) REFERENCES fitness_db.Products ( ProductID ))
UNIQUE PRIMARY INDEX ( SaleDetailID );
